    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breakage, cracking, or slippage caused by shear stress, which is the force that tends to cause deformation of a material by slippage along a plane or planes parallel to the imposed stress. Shear failure is often in reference to geological or architectural materials.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指剪應力造成的斷裂、破裂或滑動。從外部施加於材料的剪應力，使材料沿著與施力來源平行的單一平面或數個平面滑動，而造成材料變形。剪力破壞通常用來敘述地質或建築材料。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breuken, scheurvorming of verschuivingen die worden veroorzaakt door afschuifspanning, de kracht die vervorming van een materiaal kan veroorzaken door het verschuiven langs een vlak of vlakken die evenwijdig lopen aan de opgelegde spanning. Met 'afschuifbreuk' wordt vaak verwezen naar geologische of architectonische materialen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
